This paper discusses the use of software reliability growth models (SRGMs) to estimate the safety and reliability of autonomous vehicles. This topic falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with the development and testing of software systems. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in autonomous vehicles, as well as the robotics (cs.RO) aspect of their operation. The safety and reliability of autonomous vehicles also falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cyber attacks on autonomous vehicles, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
